[32m"Masked text for sample 0, segment 1860-2301: .\n\nLet me try again.\n\nTo solve this problem, we need to calculate the total amount of money the company pays to its employees over a period of three months. We can break down the problem into the following steps:\n\n1. Calculate the number of employees after three months.\n2. Calculate the total salary paid to the employees each month.\n3. Sum the total salaries paid over the three months.\n\nLet's start by calculating the number of employees after three months:\n\n- Initial number of employees: 200\n- New employees hired each month: 20\n- Number of months: 3\n\nThe number of employees after three months will be:\n\\[ 200 + 20 \\times 3 = 200 + 60 = 260 \\]\n\nNext, we calculate the total salary paid to the employees each month. Since each employee is paid $4000 per month, the total salary for one month will be:\n\\[ 200 + 20 \\times \\text{month number} \\times 4000 \\]\n\nWe can then sum the total salaries paid over the three months. Let's implement this in Python to get the accurate result.\n```python\n# Initial number of employees\ninitial_employees = 200\n\n# Number of new employees hired each month\nnew_employees_per_month = 20\n\n# Number of months\nmonths = 3\n\n# Salary per employee per month\nsalary_per_employee = 4000\n\n# Calculate the total number of employees after three months\ntotal_employees_after_three_months = initial_employees + new_employees_per_month * months\n\n# Calculate the total salary paid over the three months\ntotal_salary = sum((initial_employees + new_employees_per_month * month) * salary_per_employee for month in range(months + 1))\n\nprint(total_salary)\n```\n```output\n2880000\n```\nThe total amount of money the company pays to its employees after three months is \\(\\boxed{2880000}\\).\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\n"[0m
