[32m'Masked text for sample 1, segment 5368-5696: ).\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\nTo determine whether the given answer is correct, we can use a formula related to lattice points within a rectangle. The rectangle is defined by its vertices \\((5,4), (-5,4), (-5,-4), (5,-4)\\).\n\nFirst, calculate the dimensions of the rectangle:\n- The length along the x-axis is from \\(-5\\) to \\(5\\), which is \\(5 - (-5) = 10\\).\n- The length along the y-axis is from \\(-4\\) to \\(4\\), which is \\(4 - (-4) = 8\\).\n\nThe formula to find the number of integer lattice points strictly inside a rectangle (not on the boundary) is:\n\\[\n(m-1) \\times (n-1)\n\\]\nwhere \\(m\\) and \\(n\\) are the number of integer points along the x-axis and y-axis, respectively.\n\nFor the x-axis, the integer points range from \\(-4\\) to \\(4\\) (since \\(-5\\) and \\(5\\) are on the boundary), giving us \\(10 - 1 = 9\\) points.\nFor the y-axis, the integer points range from \\(-3\\) to \\(3\\) (since \\(-4\\) and \\(4\\) are on the boundary), giving us \\(8 - 1 = 7\\) points.\n\nThus, the number of integer points strictly inside the rectangle is:\n\\[\n9 \\times 7 = 63\n\\]\n\nTherefore, the given answer of 63 is correct.<|im_end|>\n'[0m
