[32m"Masked text for sample 1, segment 68-705: Roslyn has ten boxes. Five of the boxes contain pencils, four of the boxes contain pens, and two of the boxes contain both pens and pencils. We need to determine how many boxes contain neither pens nor pencils.\n\nTo solve this, we can use the principle of inclusion and exclusion. Here are the steps:\n\n1. Let \\( A \\) be the set of boxes containing pencils.\n2. Let \\( B \\) be the set of boxes containing pens.\n3. We are given:\n   - \\( |A| = 5 \\) (boxes with pencils)\n   - \\( |B| = 4 \\) (boxes with pens)\n   - \\( |A \\cap B| = 2 \\) (boxes with both pens and pencils)\n4. We need to find the number of boxes that contain neither pens nor pencils, which is \\( |A^c \\cap B^c| \\).\n\nUsing the principle of inclusion and exclusion, the number of boxes that contain either pens or pencils (or both) is:\n\\[ |A \\cup B| = |A| + |B| - |A \\cap B| \\]\n\nThe total number of boxes is 10. So, the number of boxes that contain neither pens nor pencils is:\n\\[ |A^c \\cap B^c| = 10 - |A \\cup B| \\]\n\nLet's compute this step-by-step using Python.\n```python\n# Given values\ntotal_boxes = 10\nboxes_with_pencils = 5\nboxes_with_pens = 4\nboxes_with_both = 2\n\n# Using the principle of inclusion and exclusion\nboxes_with_either_or_both = boxes_with_pencils + boxes_with_pens - boxes_with_both\n\n# Calculate the boxes with neither pens nor pencils\nboxes_with_neither = total_boxes - boxes_with_either_or_both\nprint(boxes_with_neither)\n```\n```output\n3\n```\nThe number of boxes that contain neither pens nor pencils is \\(\\boxed{3}\\).\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\nTo determine whether the answer is correct, we can use the principle of inclusion-exclusion.\n\n1. Total number of boxes = 10\n2. Boxes with pencils = 5\n3. Boxes with pens = 4\n4. Boxes with both pens and pencils = 2\n\nUsing the principle of inclusion-exclusion, the number of boxes with either pens or pencils (or both) is calculated as follows:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Boxes with either pens or pencils} = (\\text{Boxes with pencils}) + (\\text{Boxes with pens}) - (\\text{Boxes with both pens and pencils})\n\\]\n\nSubstituting the given values:\n\n\\[\n= 5 + 4 - 2 = 7\n\\]\n\nTherefore, the number of boxes that contain neither pens nor pencils is:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Total boxes} - \\text{Boxes with either pens or pencils} = 10 - 7 = 3\n\\]\n\nThe answer provided is 3, which is correct.<|im_end|>\n"[0m
