[32m'Masked text for sample 0, segment 4791-5417: \n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\nTo determine whether the given answer is correct, we can use the formula for the area of a triangle formed by two vectors in three-dimensional space. The area of triangle \\(OAB\\) can be found using the cross product of the vectors \\(\\overrightarrow{OA}\\) and \\(\\overrightarrow{OB}\\).\n\nThe formula for the area of the triangle is:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{2} \\|\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\|\n\\]\n\nFirst, calculate the cross product \\(\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\):\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OA} = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\\\ 2 \\\\ 3 \\end{pmatrix}, \\quad \\overrightarrow{OB} = \\begin{pmatrix} -3 \\\\ -2 \\\\ 1 \\end{pmatrix}\n\\]\n\nThe cross product \\(\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\) is given by the determinant:\n\n\\[\n\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB} = \\begin{vmatrix} \\mathbf{i} & \\mathbf{j} & \\mathbf{k} \\\\ 1 & 2 & 3 \\\\ -3 & -2 & 1 \\end{vmatrix}\n\\]\n\nCalculating this determinant:\n\n\\[\n= \\mathbf{i}(2 \\cdot 1 - 3 \\cdot (-2)) - \\mathbf{j}(1 \\cdot 1 - 3 \\cdot (-3)) + \\mathbf{k}(1 \\cdot (-2) - 2 \\cdot (-3))\n\\]\n\n\\[\n= \\mathbf{i}(2 + 6) - \\mathbf{j}(1 + 9) + \\mathbf{k}(-2 + 6)\n\\]\n\n\\[\n= \\mathbf{i}(8) - \\mathbf{j}(10) + \\mathbf{k}(4)\n\\]\n\n\\[\n= \\begin{pmatrix} 8 \\\\ -10 \\\\ 4 \\end{pmatrix}\n\\]\n\nNow, find the magnitude of this vector:\n\n\\[\n\\|\\overrightarrow{OA} \\times \\overrightarrow{OB}\\| = \\sqrt{8^2 + (-10)^2 + 4^2}\n\\]\n\n\\[\n= \\sqrt{64 + 100 + 16}\n\\]\n\n\\[\n= \\sqrt{180}\n\\]\n\n\\[\n= \\sqrt{36 \\times 5}\n\\]\n\n\\[\n= 6\\sqrt{5}\n\\]\n\nThe area of the triangle is:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 6\\sqrt{5} = 3\\sqrt{5}\n\\]\n\nThe given answer is 3, but the calculated area is \\(3\\sqrt{5}\\). Therefore, the given answer is incorrect.\n\n'[0m
