[32m"Masked text for sample 1, segment 821-1278: .\n\nLet me try again.\n\nTo solve this problem, we need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Calculate the number of chickens Isaias plans to sell.\n2. Determine the total revenue from selling these chickens.\n3. Calculate the total cost of the chickens he bought.\n4. Use the profit equation to find out how much he spent on the chickens.\n\nHere's the step-by-step breakdown:\n\n1. Calculate the number of chickens Isaias plans to sell:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Number of chickens to sell} = \\frac{3}{5} \\times 300 = 180\n   \\]\n2. Determine the total revenue from selling these chickens:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Total revenue} = 180 \\times 50 = 9000\n   \\]\n3. Let \\(C\\) be the total cost of the chickens he bought. The profit is given as $2000, and profit is calculated as total revenue minus total cost:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Profit} = \\text{Total revenue} - \\text{Total cost}\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   2000 = 9000 - C\n   \\]\n4. Solve for \\(C\\):\n   \\[\n   C = 9000 - 2000 = 7000\n   \\]\n\nSo, Isaias bought the chickens he took to the market for $7000. Let's confirm this with Python code.\n```python\n# Given values\ntotal_chickens = 300\nchickens_to_sell = (3/5) * total_chickens\nprice_per_chicken = 50\nprofit = 2000\n\n# Calculate total revenue\ntotal_revenue = chickens_to_sell * price_per_chicken\n\n# Calculate total cost\ntotal_cost = total_revenue - profit\n\nprint(total_cost)\n```\n```output\n7000.0\n```\nThe total cost Isaias paid for the chickens he took to the market for sale is \\(\\boxed{7000}\\).\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\n"[0m
