os A = \\frac{\\sqrt{5}}{5} \\quad \\text{and} \\quad \\sin A = \\frac{2\\sqrt{5}}{5}\n\\]\n\nThus, $\\tan A = \\frac{\\sin A}{\\cos A} = \\frac{\\frac{2\\sqrt{5}}{5}}{\\frac{\\sqrt{5}}{5}} = 2$.\n\nSo, the final answer is:\n\\[\n\\boxed{2}\n\\]\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\n"[0m
